theorem Topology.P3_of_open_closureInterior {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hOpen : IsOpen (closure (interior A))) : Topology.P3 A := by
  dsimp [Topology.P3]
  intro x hxA
  -- Any point of `A` is in `closure (interior A)`.
  have hx_cl : x ∈ closure (interior A) := subset_closure hxA
  -- Since this closure is open, its interior is itself.
  have hx_int : x ∈ interior (closure (interior A)) := by
    have hEq : interior (closure (interior A)) = closure (interior A) :=
      hOpen.interior_eq
    simpa [hEq] using hx_cl
  -- Use the established inclusion to land in `interior (closure A)`.
  have hIncl : interior (closure (interior A)) ⊆ interior (closure A) :=
    interiorClosureInterior_subset_interiorClosure (A := A)
  exact hIncl hx_int
